 {"id":"bd-191m","title":"[FCP2] Agent-Side Caching: ETag and Cache-Control Support","description":"# [FCP2] Agent-Side Caching: ETag and Cache-Control Support

## Goal
Enable efficient agent-side caching of discovery and introspection responses to reduce latency and host load.

## Problem
Agents frequently call discovery/introspect endpoints to get connector and tool information. Currently:
- Every call hits the host even if nothing changed
- No way for agents to know if their cached data is stale
- Wastes resources re-fetching identical data

## Solution: HTTP Caching Semantics for JSON-RPC

### Response Headers (Extension)

Add optional cache metadata to JSON-RPC responses:

```jsonc
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "result": {
    "connectors": [...],
    "_meta": {
      "cache": {
        "etag": "\"abc123def456\"",
        "last_modified": "2026-01-22T18:00:00Z",
        "max_age_seconds": 300,
        "stale_while_revalidate_seconds": 60
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Conditional Request Support

Agents can include cache validators in requests:

```jsonc
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "connectors/discover",
  "params": {
    "_cache": {
      "if_none_match": "\"abc123def456\"",
      "if_modified_since": "2026-01-22T18:00:00Z"
    }
  }
}
```

### 304 Not Modified Response

If cache is still valid, host returns a lightweight response:

```jsonc
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "result": {
    "_meta": {
      "status": 304,
      "message": "Not Modified",
      "cache": {
        "etag": "\"abc123def456\"",
        "max_age_seconds": 300
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Implementation

```rust
pub struct CacheMetadata {
    /// Strong ETag for content comparison
    pub etag: String,
    /// Last modification timestamp
    pub last_modified: DateTime<Utc>,
    /// Seconds before client should revalidate
    pub max_age_seconds: u32,
    /// Seconds to serve stale while revalidating
    pub stale_while_revalidate_seconds: Option<u32>,
}

pub struct CacheValidator {
    pub if_none_match: Option<String>,
    pub if_modified_since: Option<DateTime<Utc>>,
}

impl DiscoveryEndpoint {
    pub async fn discover_with_cache(
        &self,
        filter: Option<DiscoveryFilter>,
        validator: Option<CacheValidator>,
    ) -> DiscoveryResponse {
        // Check if registry has changed
        let current_etag = self.registry.content_hash();
        let current_modified = self.registry.last_modified();

        if let Some(v) = validator {
            // Check ETag match
            if let Some(client_etag) = v.if_none_match {
                if client_etag == current_etag {
                    return DiscoveryResponse::not_modified(current_etag);
                }
            }
            // Check modification time
            if let Some(client_modified) = v.if_modified_since {
                if current_modified <= client_modified {
                    return DiscoveryResponse::not_modified(current_etag);
                }
            }
        }

        // Fetch fresh data
        let connectors = self.registry.list_filtered(filter).await;
        DiscoveryResponse {
            connectors,
            cache: CacheMetadata {
                etag: current_etag,
                last_modified: current_modified,
                max_age_seconds: 300,
                stale_while_revalidate_seconds: Some(60),
            },
        }
    }
}

/// ETag generation for registry content
impl ConnectorRegistry {
    pub fn content_hash(&self) -> String {
        use sha2::{Sha256, Digest};
        let mut hasher = Sha256::new();

        // Hash all connector summaries
        for connector in self.connectors.values() {
            hasher.update(connector.id.as_bytes());
            hasher.update(connector.version.to_string().as_bytes());
            hasher.update(&[connector.enabled as u8]);
        }

        format!("\"{}\"", hex::encode(&hasher.finalize()[..8]))
    }

    pub fn last_modified(&self) -> DateTime<Utc> {
        self.connectors.values()
            .map(|c| c.installed_at)
            .max()
            .unwrap_or(self.created_at)
    }
}
```

### Cacheable Endpoints

| Method | Recommended max_age | ETag Source |
|--------|---------------------|-------------|
| `connectors/discover` | 5 min | Registry content hash |
| `connectors/introspect` | 15 min | Connector version + config |
| `host/capabilities` | 1 hour | Host version |
| `tools/list` | 5 min | Tool registry hash |

### Tests

```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_discover_returns_cache_metadata() {
    let host = TestHost::new().await;
    host.install_connector("test-echo").await;

    let response = host.discover(None, None).await.unwrap();
    assert!(!response.cache.etag.is_empty());
    assert!(response.cache.max_age_seconds > 0);
}

#[tokio::test]
async fn test_conditional_request_returns_304() {
    let host = TestHost::new().await;
    host.install_connector("test-echo").await;

    // First request - get ETag
    let r1 = host.discover(None, None).await.unwrap();
    let etag = r1.cache.etag.clone();

    // Conditional request with same ETag
    let validator = CacheValidator { if_none_match: Some(etag), if_modified_since: None };
    let r2 = host.discover(None, Some(validator)).await.unwrap();

    assert_eq!(r2.meta.status, 304);
    assert!(r2.connectors.is_none()); // No body on 304
}

#[tokio::test]
async fn test_etag_changes_on_registry_update() {
    let host = TestHost::new().await;
    host.install_connector("test-echo").await;

    let r1 = host.discover(None, None).await.unwrap();
    let etag1 = r1.cache.etag.clone();

    // Install another connector
    host.install_connector("test-streaming").await;

    let r2 = host.discover(None, None).await.unwrap();
    assert_ne!(r1.cache.etag, r2.cache.etag);
}

#[tokio::test]
async fn test_stale_etag_returns_fresh_data() {
    let host = TestHost::new().await;
    host.install_connector("test-echo").await;

    let r1 = host.discover(None, None).await.unwrap();
    let old_etag = r1.cache.etag.clone();

    // Modify registry
    host.install_connector("test-streaming").await;

    // Conditional request with stale ETag
    let validator = CacheValidator { if_none_match: Some(old_etag), if_modified_since: None };
    let r2 = host.discover(None, Some(validator)).await.unwrap();

    assert_ne!(r2.meta.status, 304);
    assert_eq!(r2.connectors.as_ref().unwrap().len(), 2);
}

#[tokio::test]
async fn test_if_modified_since_validation() {
    let host = TestHost::new().await;
    host.install_connector("test-echo").await;

    let r1 = host.discover(None, None).await.unwrap();
    let last_modified = r1.cache.last_modified;

    // Request with if-modified-since after last modification
    let validator = CacheValidator {
        if_none_match: None,
        if_modified_since: Some(last_modified + Duration::seconds(1)),
    };
    let r2 = host.discover(None, Some(validator)).await.unwrap();

    assert_eq!(r2.meta.status, 304);
}
```

